So, I'm confused. You want the start button to be on the bottom when you put it onto the left side of your screen? I think that may have been fixed. I tried that with my computer and the start button goes to the bottom. <br />Also, that's not really the problem with classic shell, it's just how Windows 10 works. Maybe, there could be a way to put the start button onto the other side using Classic Shell. I might ask Ivo about this.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=16614">AcroGen</a> — Sat Jan 07, 2017 4:22 pm</p><hr />
